  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The serratus anterior plan (SAP) block is a technique that has recently gained popularity in&#xD;
      the context of breast surgery. SAP block resulted in better hemodynamic stability, early&#xD;
      ambulation and shorter hospital stay, as well as hospital costs for postoperative breast&#xD;
      patients.&#xD;
&#xD;
      We aimed to investigate the effects of the serratus anterior plane block in women undergoing&#xD;
      breast surgery, in the intraoperative period.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
